reviews.text:
Food was tasty, especially the platters and falafel. The lamb and filet were on the dryer side but the rice pilaf texture was amazing. The space is small and service was almost non-existent which was surprising given how small it is. We had to reach out for basic things. When we did speak with someone they were nice and helpful.

I don‚Äôt recommend getting the charred octopus. For $22 we got ONE small tentacle on top of lentils. Vastly overpriced and flavor did not make up for it
This Armenian restaurant is so so good! Such delicious food. If you like Middle Eastern food in general you owe it to yourself to visit this place!

Food was DELICIOUS here! Can't wait to go back! Our server Julia was so wonderful and patient with us explaining the different dishes. This place is a hidden gem in northern liberties, we'll definitely be back! Thank You!

Ok. First off. Great food, hands down. As a person who has traveled to the Middle East and Mediterranean, this is some high-quality food. They clearly are a family from the counties in which the food is served and the food is authentic. If stopping in, they have a selection of dishes for two people that allows you to choose, and it is delicious! The skewers, the eggplant, the hummus, the tabbouleh was fantastic. The atmosphere was a little lacking but it's ok because it felt like a family-oreiented place, and the service mirrored that. I felt special just eating there. I am looking forward to coming again. If you crave Middle Eastern Arabic/Greek food, you need to go there. It is worth the time!
Excellent food, generous portions, tasteful seasoning.  Staff were attentive and atmosphere comfortable.  Hope to be back soon!

detailedReviews.text: Absolutely amazing restaurant. Starting off with the food, absolutely amazing. The flavors are out of this world, hard to find such rich and flavorful food but this place hit it out of the ballpark. Our server, Ani(sorry if mispelled) was the sweetest and most accommodating ever. It was a birthday dinner and she did not miss a beat, she made it so special and she was so personable and fun to talk to. Our water was always full, the bussers always kept the table clean of plates that we finished eating from. As someone in the restaurant industry this was such a wholesome experience. Recommend this cute little place to everyone was such a great find!

detailedReviews.author: Talar Foti
detailedReviews.text: Apricot Stone is an absolute gem! If you're craving authentic Armenian cuisine, this place delivers on every level. The food is delicious ‚Äî every dish we tried was full of bold, comforting flavors that feel both traditional and elevated.  We especially loved the Manti ‚Äî they were cooked to perfection and beautifully presented. The Mujaddara was another standout. The lentils were full of flavor, the dish was so well-balanced and satisfying.  The ambiance is warm and inviting ‚Äî a perfect setting for a relaxed dinner or special occasion. We came from NYC to celebrate a birthday and it ended up being such a special night. We loved the modern Armenian music and art that decorated the restaurant. The staff were friendly and knowledgeable, they worked tirelessly with a full house.  Whether you‚Äôre new to Armenian food or grew up with it, Apricot Stone offers an experience that‚Äôs both comforting and memorable. Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.author: Hollei
detailedReviews.text: Every now and again, I stumble across a restaurant that is a complete gem & a diamond in the rough. This, place was both. I found it on IG. A influencer posted for Northern Liberties restaurant week highlighting this place, and from what I saw, I had to have it. I've been doing restaurant weeks in the city and on the outskirts for many many years now. I have never had an experience where I've received so much delicious food for my money ($45). I came here with two other friends for the first week of Northern Liberties restaurant week. With my first experience, just off of the taste and the amount of food that I got I knew I had to come back before restaurant week was over. I made my second visit on the Saturday of the last day of restaurant week. My friend and I dined in for my second time and had an extraordinary experience. We got the abundance of food for just $45, accompanied by the generosity of the owner, who opened the bottle of his own tequila and poured shots from it for free. He was very interactive, and very personable. Anytime an owner is that involved and nice to their customers, they get me. He asked me my name, and addressed me every single time afterwards by it. And because of the simple gesture, and the delicious food... They've got a customer that will keep coming back. I will support this business as long as it's around. The staff is very nice & the space is very quaint.

detailedReviews.text: Tried to make a reservation for a large party of moms who have our kids at an event down the street. No mention of $50 min pp requirement for large parties over 7 people on website etc. Host was rude about it. Will go elsewhere.

detailedReviews.author: Serena N.
detailedReviews.text:
Amazing food and service. We tried quite a bit of the items on the menu and everything was very good. Our favorites were the imam bayaldi, israeli salad, and the spanikopida. All of the vegetables were very fresh and everything was flavorful.

It seems like they changed locations not that long ago, so watch out if you take an Uber or Lyft, as those might take you to the old location!

detailedReviews.author: Shelby Dove
detailedReviews.text: Apricot Stone was just fine but a good value. The service felt rushed and they didn't give any guidance on how to approach the menu. We had a trio of dips, the falafel, and chicken shawarma. The rice that came with the chicken was my favorite part of the meal. It was a good amount of food and the BYOB aspect is nice.

detailedReviews.author: Krikor A
detailedReviews.text: Everything about this place is top notch. The food is consistently incredible you won‚Äôt have a bad morsel touch your mouth. So delicious honestly we have literally tried everything on the menu and it is all amazing! The kids love it, we love it and everyone we bring here loves it. Great for dates, double dates, or large group gatherings. They have a bunch of different spaces so you can easily have a party of be more private, definitely need to check this place out if you love good food and you will get great atmosphere and service as a bonus!!!!
